I have closed Wagoner Rural Gas Authority. I have no customers left on my pipeline effective February 18, 2019. All customers converted to electric or propane. All gas was purged from line, no gas left in my pipeline. Oklahoma Natural Gas shut down my pipeline per my request.

(1)West Lincoln Natural Gas District maintains and operates a 2" main of PE 30.33 miles in northwest Lincoln County, Ms. WLNG operates on daily basis of 55-58 psi with MAOP of 67 psi for the system. (2)WLNG's supplier of gas is Centerpoint Energy Services with the gas being taken at Gulf South Pipeline meter station. The transportation of the gas is by Southeast Gas Transmission along a 6.5 mile 8" steel pipeline. (3)The odorization of the gas is done by Southeast Gas with a system by King Tool 1-B with an OD 6 5/8" holding 2.2 gallons of odorant with an odorant reserve tank on site that contains 55 gallons. It's maximum capacity is 150,000 SCFH. Odorator used in field by WLNG is a Heath Consultant odorator that is one of the newest. Any abnormal readings over 1.00 are discussed with Southeast Gas Transmission and adjustments are made by them on injection levels. (4)New updated Operation & Maintenance with Emergencies Procedural Manual was completed for the system in March 2018. (5) Map of entire system is available for anyone to view but is given in detail to the 2 County Supervisors within our system.
